  <prompt>
    Close real-bug-ledger entry **RB-T044-02** by fixing the production bug in `CitationExtractor.NormalizeCaseLaw`. The `TrimEnd('.')` call at line 167 over-strips the canonical trailing period of US Supreme Court reporter abbreviations (e.g., `U.S.`), violating the documented canonical-key contract.

    The ledger's recommended fix: **remove `.TrimEnd('.')`** from line 167 — the reporter capture group already excludes the trailing year-court parenthetical, so no additional trim is needed.

    Per D-02, this single production fix closes ONE ledger entry. Per NFR-04, the commit message MUST cite `RB-T044-02` + resolution mode `repaired`. Per NFR-02, line replacement <50% in the file. After the fix, remove the `Skip = "..."` attribute on the affected Theory (`ExtractCitations_CaseLaw_MatchedAndNormalized`, 4 InlineData) and flip per-Theory `[Trait("status","real-bug-pending-fix")]` to inherit class-level `repaired`.
  </prompt>

  <role>Backend AI agent fixing production code in `Services/Ai/Safety/Citations/` to close a MEDIUM-severity real-bug ledger entry.</role>

  <goal>
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety/Citations/CitationExtractor.cs` `NormalizeCaseLaw` method no longer applies `TrimEnd('.')`. The 4 affected InlineData cases in `ExtractCitations_CaseLaw_MatchedAndNormalized` Theory flip Skip → Pass. The ledger entry RB-T044-02 transitions from `assigned-to-r2` → `repaired`. Existing Statute / Regulation / Patent test cases remain green.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
