  <context>
    <background>
      `CitationExtractor` is one of the Layer-1 citation normalization stages used by `Services/Ai/Safety/*` for verification provider lookups + UI display. Per the class XML doc at line 11, canonical key for `Smith v. Jones, 542 U.S. 296 (2004)` is `"542 U.S. 296"` — the trailing period of `U.S.` is part of the canonical form. The current implementation calls `.TrimEnd('.')` defensively, producing `"542 U.S. 296"` → `"542 U.S. 296"` for most cases but failing the 4 reporter-period InlineData cases. The bug surfaces only when the reporter abbreviation itself ends in a period.

      r2 Phase 2 Wave 1 (this wave) targets MEDIUM-severity entries; parallel-safe across disjoint file sets. This task and task 021 (NormalizePatent EP/WO double-prefix) BOTH touch `CitationExtractor.cs` — they CANNOT run in parallel. Task 020 (this one) runs first; task 021 runs in the next sub-wave AFTER this commit lands.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="013" status="required">Phase 1 exit triple-run validated; baseline green</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety/Citations/CitationExtractor.cs</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Safety/CitationExtractorTests.cs</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load the RB-T044-02 ledger entry (`projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/real-bug-ledger.md` lines 289-323). Confirm Status is `open` or `assigned-to-r2`; if `repaired` or `archived`, abort with a note.</step>
    <step order="2">Read `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety/Citations/CitationExtractor.cs` `NormalizeCaseLaw` method (around line 163). Verify the `.TrimEnd('.')` call is at line 167 as documented; if drift, capture exact line.</step>
    <step order="3">Read `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Safety/CitationExtractorTests.cs` `ExtractCitations_CaseLaw_MatchedAndNormalized` Theory. Note the 4 InlineData cases + the per-Theory `[Trait("status","real-bug-pending-fix")]` override + the Skip attribute.</step>
    <step order="4">Apply the production fix: remove `.TrimEnd('.')` from `NormalizeCaseLaw` line 167. Verify no other call sites in the method also strip the period. Confirm the method returns the expected canonical key for all 4 InlineData cases by hand-tracing the regex captures.</step>
    <step order="5">Remove the `Skip = "..."` attribute and the per-Theory `[Trait("status","real-bug-pending-fix")]` override on `ExtractCitations_CaseLaw_MatchedAndNormalized`. The class-level `[Trait("status","repaired")]` will then apply.</step>
    <step order="6">Build: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`. Verify 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="7">Run targeted tests: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~CitationExtractorTests"`. Confirm all 4 InlineData cases pass + Statute/Regulation/Patent Theory cases still pass.</step>
    <step order="8">Step 9.5 quality gates: run `code-review` + `adr-check` (FULL rigor). Verify the change is <50% line replacement; verify no new DI registrations (ADR-010); verify AI/Safety service stays in-process (ADR-013).</step>
    <step order="9">Update RB-T044-02 ledger entry: transition Status to `repaired`; add fix-commit SHA + date.</step>
    <step order="10">Commit: `fix(ai/safety): remove TrimEnd('.') from CitationExtractor.NormalizeCaseLaw (RB-T044-02; repaired)`. Update `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/current-task.md` with completion summary.</step>
  </steps>

